Ticket ID: SEC-INC-2026-01-LAPTOPII-DRIVER-AUTOMATION
Title: Laptop II — System Instability and Windows Update Failure Following Driver Automation
Date: 03 January 2026
Classification: Operating System Instability / Driver Stack Corruption / Windows Update Servicing Failure
Status: Escalated – Strategic Decision for Clean OS Reinstallation
Priority: Critical
Affected Asset: Laptop II (High-Performance Laptop Workstation, AMD Platform)
Related Tickets: SEC-INC-2026-02-LAPTOPII-SERVICING, SEC-DEV-2025-12-LAPTOPII

Executive Summary
Laptop II experienced severe system instability and Windows Update servicing failure following aggressive automated driver installation using third-party driver automation tools.
Initial instability manifested as system freezes and crashes. Although runtime stability was later restored through extensive remediation, major Windows Updates—including cumulative security updates and feature upgrades—remained permanently blocked.
Root cause analysis identified incompatible and unstable driver installations introduced by automated tools, resulting in corruption of Windows servicing components and long-term servicing stack inconsistency.
Due to persistent servicing failures and elevated long-term security risk, a strategic decision was made to perform a clean Windows reinstallation using a controlled driver installation methodology.
