The system supported two operational profiles:
Performance Mode (Plugged-In)
	• Maximum CPU performance
	• Maximum GPU performance
	• Aggressive cooling and performance tuning
Battery Optimization Mode
	• Reduced CPU power states
	• Optimized GPU power usage
	• Extended battery runtime configuration
Profiles were managed using official vendor utilities, Windows power plans, and system optimization tools. Long-term objectives included automation of profile switching using scripted logic or AI-assisted tools.
